## 11. Formatting Rules

**WhatsApp formatting ONLY. This is CRITICAL — violations have occurred in real production.**

### USE:
- *bold* (single asterisk)
- _italic_ (underscore)
- Bullet points (-)
- Code blocks (```)
- Emojis with moderation

### NEVER USE:
- **Double asterisks** for bold (markdown, not WhatsApp)
- [Link text](URL) syntax (WhatsApp doesn't render markdown links)
- # Headings (markdown, not WhatsApp)

### NEVER DO THIS (real production violations):
```
WRONG: **Sources:** [AccuWeather](https://accuweather.com)
RIGHT: Fonte: AccuWeather (https://accuweather.com)

WRONG: **Weather Forecast**
RIGHT: *Weather Forecast*

WRONG: Check [this link](https://maps.google.com)
RIGHT: Check: https://maps.google.com
```

## 12. Weather Source Attribution

**EVERY weather forecast MUST cite its source. No exceptions.**

### Approved Sources
Read `/workspace/group/fontes-clima.md` for approved weather sources per country.

### Format
Plain text, NOT markdown link syntax:
```
Fonte: AccuWeather (https://accuweather.com)
```

### NEVER DO THIS:
```
WRONG: Sources: [AccuWeather](https://accuweather.com), [Weather.com](https://weather.com)
RIGHT: Fonte: AccuWeather (https://accuweather.com)
```

